cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the design of a wireless communication device and introduces a save-then-transmit protocol to optimize the system performance. This involves analyzing the outage probability and deriving the optimal save-ratio, which are typical topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the extension of the proposed protocol to wireless networks with multiple transmitters, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers the constraint of energy half-duplex and the use of two rechargeable energy storage devices, which can be viewed as a control system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions data transmission, which can be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper involves the design of a wireless communication device relying exclusively on energy harvesting, which may require hardware architecture considerations.
